{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b012567e-650d-46b9-8921-8d0258809bde","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options:**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant (org) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Single-org Azure AD auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain contoso.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# No auth (default)\ndotnet new webapi\n```\n\nYou can also add `--use-minimal-apis` for minimal API style or explore all options with `dotnet new webapi --help`.\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc0c6165-b499-4212-80f8-e7c8e4ec9c7e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/programming question rather than something specific to the codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nActually, let me check if there's relevant context in the current working directory or if this is related to the repository's plugins (like the dotnet plugin).","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"AC45:36731D:FFA78:13BA89:69F549FA"},"id":"9e132200-6f1d-4a58-852e-7afeae85cd6c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:06.982Z","parentId":"b2a66a80-c1e8-4a00-aa45-42e51e6a663b"}
